# Testing

The authoritative test plan lives in `docs/test_plan_and_strategy.mdc`.
The developer testing workflow is documented in `docs/developers_guide.mdc`.
Always consult those files for test levels, fixture strategy, and the full test matrix.

Key conventions (see test plan for full details):

- Test runner: `pytest >= 8.0`, tests in `tests/`, naming: `test_<module>.py`
- Shared fixtures in `tests/conftest.py`; all I/O tests use `tmp_path`
- Synthetic `.eml` fixtures in `tests/fixtures/emails/` with subdirectories
- Receipt images generated with Pillow `ImageDraw` in test setup
- Never commit real user data; use clearly synthetic names/amounts
- Patch `requests.post` directly for LLM mocks (not module-level)
